Code Academey - (C++ for beginers )




Common link-time errors :

 1) * Using a function that was never defined 
  
        ***
 
 
 2) *Writing Main() insted of mamin()
      
     -   https://content.codecademy.com/courses/learn-cpp/loops/link-time-error.png
     
     
     
     Find whats wrong with the code -
     
     
  #include <iostream>

int Main() {
  
  int num = 0;
  int sum = 0;
  
  std::cout << "Enter a number: ";
  std::cin >> num;
  
  for (int i = 1; i <= num; i++) {
    
    sum = sum + i;
    std::cout << i << " ";
    
  }
  
  std::cout << "Sum: " << sum << "\n";
  
}



???????????????
answer 
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>

Writing Main() insted of mamin()


